{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Train Blueprint Analysis Model with YOLOv8\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook is designed to run on Google Colab to train your AI blueprint analysis model using a free cloud GPU.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Before you start:**\n",
    "1. Go to **Runtime > Change runtime type** and select **T4 GPU**.\n",
    "2. Upload your `blueprint_dataset.zip` file to your Google Drive (e.g., inside a folder named `Blueprints`)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Install the required Ultralytics package\n",
    "!pip install ultralytics"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Mount Google Drive\n",
    "We need to connect your Google Drive so the notebook can read your dataset and save the trained model."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from google.colab import drive\n",
    "drive.mount('/content/drive')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Unzip Dataset\n",
    "We will extract the pre-formatted YOLO dataset directly to the Colab instance for fast reading during training.\n",
    "**IMPORTANT:** Update `zip_path` if your file is in a different location in your Drive."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "import zipfile\n",
    "\n",
    "# Change this path if your data is stored elsewhere in your Drive\n",
    "zip_path = \"/content/drive/MyDrive/Blueprints/blueprint_dataset.zip\"\n",
    "extract_dir = \"/content/datasets\"\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Extracting {zip_path}...\")\n",
    "os.makedirs(extract_dir, exist_ok=True)\n",
    "with zipfile.ZipFile(zip_path, 'r') as zip_ref:\n",
    "    zip_ref.extractall(extract_dir)\n",
    "print(\"Extraction complete!\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Fix YAML Paths\n",
    "The `data.yaml` file was generated on Windows and contains a Windows path. We need to update it to the Colab path."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import yaml\n",
    "\n",
    "yaml_path = '/content/datasets/blueprints_large/data.yaml'\n",
    "\n",
    "with open(yaml_path, 'r') as f:\n",
    "    data = yaml.safe_load(f)\n",
    "\n",
    "data['path'] = '/content/datasets/blueprints_large'\n",
    "\n",
    "with open(yaml_path, 'w') as f:\n",
    "    yaml.dump(data, f, default_flow_style=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"YAML path updated to:\", data['path'])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Train YOLOv8 Model\n",
    "Now we train the model. We use `yolov8m.pt` (Medium) for high accuracy, and run for 100 epochs."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from ultralytics import YOLO\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load a pre-trained Medium model\n",
    "model = YOLO('yolov8m.pt') \n",
    "\n",
    "# Train for 100 epochs using the GPU (device=0)\n",
    "results = model.train(\n",
    "    data=\"/content/datasets/blueprints_large/data.yaml\",\n",
    "    epochs=100,\n",
    "    imgsz=640,\n",
    "    batch=16,\n",
    "    device=0,\n",
    "    project='/content/runs',\n",
    "    name='blueprint_model'\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Save the Final Model\n",
    "Once training is finished, we copy the best weights back to your Google Drive so you can download it to your PC."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import shutil\n",
    "\n",
    "source_model = \"/content/runs/blueprint_model/weights/best.pt\"\n",
    "drive_base_path = \"/content/drive/MyDrive/Blueprints\"\n",
    "dest_model = os.path.join(drive_base_path, \"best_blueprint_model.pt\")\n",
    "\n",
    "shutil.copy2(source_model, dest_model)\n",
    "print(f\"Model saved to Google Drive at: {dest_model}\")\n",
    "print(\"You can now download it from Google Drive and replace your local best.pt file!\")"
   ]
  }
 ],
